text: S Club 8 were a British pop group. They formed in 2001 in London as S Club Juniors. They released their first single and album in 2002. They were renamed in 2003 and split in 2005. Its members were: Jay Asforis (born 1989), Daisy Evans (born 1989), Calvin Goldspink (born 1989), Stacey McClean (born 1989), Aaron Renfree (born 1987), Hannah Richings (born 1990), Frankie Sandford (born 1989) and Rochelle Wiseman (born 1989). == Other websites == *S Club 8 World Category:2001 establishments in England Category:2000s British music groups Category:2005 disestablishments in England Category:British pop music groups Category:Musical groups established in 2001 Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2005 Category:Musical groups from London
